SICELO Gcwensa (27) said he can&rsquo;t believe that people escaped with their lives when a car landed in their shack.He and two friends were in his shack in Bellair Road, Cato Manor on Saturday night when they heard a loud bang.&ldquo;We ran outside and saw that a car had smashed into a shack three shacks away from mine. &ldquo;We rushed there and found the car in the shack. We helped the three people who were hurt and called the cops,&rdquo; said Sicelo.He said he does not know the injured people.Resident Mdumiseni Cebekhulu (24) said if the people had been asleep, they would have died. &ldquo;The car came to rest on top of the bed that was in the shack,&rdquo; he said.Rescue Care spokesman Garrith Jamieson said paramedics arrived at about 7pm to find that a car had crashed into a shack. &ldquo;Three occupants sustained injuries and were stabilised at the scene before being transported to a nearby hospital for further care,&rdquo; he said.Attempts to speak to the three injured people and the driver of the car failed as the SunTeam couldn&rsquo;t trace them.KZN police spokeswoman Captain Nqobile Gwala confirmed the incident although no case was opened.Councillor Warren Burne told the People&rsquo;s Paper: &ldquo;I&rsquo;m aware of the incident but couldn&rsquo;t attend to it because of other commitments. &ldquo;The police and emergency services were there, so it was all under control.&rdquo;